Introduction

Park Jung Soo, better known by his stage name Leeteuk, is a South Korean singer and TV Personality. He is known for being the leader, vocalist, and sub-rapper of the boy group SUPER JUNIOR and its sub-units, Super Junior-T and Super Junior-H under Label SJ, a subsidiary of SM Entertainment.
